WEBVTT

00:04.733 --> 00:05.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.733 --> 00:06.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:06.733 --> 00:07.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight:

00:07.733 --> 00:09.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
WOMAN: Mr. McCain, aye.

00:09.733 --> 00:13.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: A dramatic
return for John McCain, as
Republicans muster just enough

00:15.866 --> 00:19.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
votes in the Senate to move
ahead on health care, but the
future of replacing Obamacare

00:19.966 --> 00:20.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
is far from clear.

00:20.733 --> 00:22.700 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Then:

00:22.700 --> 00:26.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the
United States: I am disappointed
in the attorney general.

00:27.900 --> 00:29.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He shouldn't have
recused himself.

00:29.966 --> 00:33.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: President Trump
takes aim at Jeff Sessions,
publicly airing frustrations

00:33.433 --> 00:38.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
with his own attorney
general, as talks of
a replacement ramp up.

00:38.333 --> 00:43.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Plus: Mr. Trump's son-in-law
and top adviser, Jared Kushner,
heads back to Capitol Hill.

00:45.400 --> 00:49.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
We talk to two members
of Congress who are
asking questions about
Russian meddling.

00:51.966 --> 00:55.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And feeding children after
the school year - - how a food
bank is helping fill in the

00:56.766 --> 00:58.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
gap during summer, so
kids don't go hungry.

00:58.900 --> 01:03.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JACKIE CAMBRIDGE, Meal Service
Manager: There's always a whew
when we get it out the door.

01:05.666 --> 01:09.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And then we just hope that
it's getting to kids in need,
and that they're enjoying it,

01:09.300 --> 01:11.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and we do it all
again the next day.

01:11.033 --> 01:16.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's "PBS NewsHour."

01:18.466 --> 01:21.266 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:21.266 --> 01:26.266 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The United
States Senate tonight
has begun debating what
to do about Obamacare

01:31.366 --> 01:33.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
after weeks of waiting.

01:33.666 --> 01:38.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Republicans finally mustered
the votes to proceed in a
showdown today, with the aid

01:38.166 --> 01:42.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of a cancer patient and a
vice presidential tiebreaker.

01:42.200 --> 01:44.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Lisa Desjardins
begins our coverage.

01:44.366 --> 01:49.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: In the Senate
today, high-stakes politics
with high-volume drama.

01:54.100 --> 01:59.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
As the health care vote began,
protesters chanted "Kill the
bill" and "Shame" from the

01:59.033 --> 02:00.600 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Senate gallery.

02:00.600 --> 02:05.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
After they were removed, the
vote itself was in doubt.

02:06.933 --> 02:10.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Republican Senator Susan
Collins of Maine and Lisa
Murkowski of Alaska voted no.

02:10.366 --> 02:13.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
One more no, and the
debate would be blocked.

02:13.100 --> 02:18.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
All eyes were on Wisconsin
Republican Ron Johnson, who
didn't initially vote at all.

02:18.033 --> 02:22.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He spent minutes speaking with
GOP Leader Mitch McConnell,
before he finally voted yes.

02:22.500 --> 02:26.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MIKE PENCE, Vice President of
the United States: On this vote,
the yeas 50 and the nays are

02:26.700 --> 02:28.733 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
50.

02:28.733 --> 02:32.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The Senate, being
equally divided, the
vice president votes in
the affirmative, and the

02:32.166 --> 02:34.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
motion is agreed to.

02:34.233 --> 02:38.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Vice
President Mike Pence cast
the tiebreaking 51st vote.

02:38.733 --> 02:39.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Majority Leader McConnell:

02:39.733 --> 02:41.800 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

02:41.800 --> 02:43.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MITCH MCCONNELL (R-KY),
Majority Leader: We have
wrestled with this issue.

02:43.133 --> 02:46.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We have watched the
consequences of the status quo.

02:46.200 --> 02:51.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The people who sent us here
expect us to begin this debate.

02:53.300 --> 02:55.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Adding to the
emotion, the return of Arizona
Senator John McCain following

02:55.900 --> 02:57.866 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
his diagnosis with brain cancer.

02:57.866 --> 02:59.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He voted for debate.

02:59.366 --> 03:01.433 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

03:01.433 --> 03:03.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN MCCAIN (R), Arizona: I
voted for the motion to proceed
to allow debate to continue

03:03.266 --> 03:04.700 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and amendments be offered.

03:04.700 --> 03:09.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I will not vote for this
bill as it is today.

03:10.866 --> 03:12.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It's a shell of
a bill right now.

03:12.133 --> 03:14.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We all know that.

03:14.133 --> 03:17.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: It's still far
from clear what, if any bill
will ultimately emerge from

03:17.300 --> 03:19.366 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the Senate.

03:19.366 --> 03:22.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The multiple versions include
the original Senate bill, with
dramatic reductions in Medicaid

03:22.900 --> 03:25.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and an end to most
of Obamacare's taxes.

03:25.600 --> 03:30.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Congressional Budget Office
said it would leave 22 million
more people uninsured by

03:31.066 --> 03:33.033 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
2026.

03:33.033 --> 03:37.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Last week came talk of a full
repeal bill, with a replacement
to be determined later.

03:37.366 --> 03:42.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That would mean 32 million
more uninsured if no
replacement is ever enacted.

03:44.333 --> 03:47.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And, finally, what's
called a skinny repeal,
ending Obamacare's
individual mandate, but

03:48.200 --> 03:49.633 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
not much else.

03:49.633 --> 03:54.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It would likely add another
15 million uninsured.

03:54.033 --> 03:58.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Democrats remained uniformly
opposed, and their leader, Chuck
Schumer, condemned Republican

03:58.266 --> 03:59.266 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
maneuvering.

03:59.266 --> 04:01.366 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

04:01.366 --> 04:03.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHUCK SCHUMER (D-NY), Minority
Leader: Now the best the
majority leader's been able to

04:03.466 --> 04:06.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
cook up is a vague plan to
do whatever it takes to pass
something, anything, to get

04:09.233 --> 04:14.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the bill to a House and Senate
conference on health care.

04:15.366 --> 04:19.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
My colleagues, plain
and simple, it's a ruse.

04:21.833 --> 04:25.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The likeliest result of a
conference between the House
and Senate is full repeal of the

04:27.400 --> 04:31.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Affordable Care Act, or
something very close to it.

04:31.600 --> 04:35.533 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: From the
other end of Pennsylvania
Avenue, President Trump
hailed the vote to

04:35.533 --> 04:37.666 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
start debate.

04:37.666 --> 04:41.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
DONALD TRUMP, President
of the United States:
I want to congratulate
American people, because

04:41.133 --> 04:43.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
we're going to give
you great health care.

04:43.533 --> 04:47.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And we're going to get rid of
Obamacare, which should've been
frankly terminated long Ago.

04:47.500 --> 04:49.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It's been a disaster
for the American people.

04:49.900 --> 04:54.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: As for the
House, Majority Leader Kevin
McCarthy said, today, his caucus

04:54.233 --> 04:55.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
is waiting for the
Senate's next move.

04:55.933 --> 04:57.633 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

04:57.633 --> 04:59.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
KEVIN MCCARTHY (R-CA),
House Majority Leader:
We will be on call.

04:59.733 --> 05:02.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
At any time that the Senate
is able to pass a health care
bill -- we have already passed

05:04.333 --> 05:09.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
one -- that we will call the
House back in to finish the job.

05:11.200 --> 05:13.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: But when
that day might come, if it
comes, remains a mystery.

05:13.966 --> 05:17.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Again, the vote today
was just to start debate.

05:17.300 --> 05:21.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Over the next two days
and likely nights,
we will see scores of
amendments and amendment

05:21.966 --> 05:23.800 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
votes on the Senate floor.

05:23.800 --> 05:25.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Any senator can
offer an amendment.

05:25.900 --> 05:30.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In fact, Democrat Chris
Murphy says, Judy, he has
got 100 ready to propose.

05:30.133 --> 05:32.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, Lisa,
tell us more about how
this is going to work.

05:32.966 --> 05:37.300 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Republicans have
been saying, for example,
there is going to be a
vote on straight repeal.

05:37.300 --> 05:38.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
When would that be?

05:38.300 --> 05:39.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: Right.

05:39.700 --> 05:41.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
This is going to be important
to follow the process.

05:41.833 --> 05:45.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Votes could happen as
soon as tonight, though
I'm told by sources in
both parties that that's

05:45.200 --> 05:46.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
unlikely at this time.

05:46.766 --> 05:48.666 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Here's how it's likely to work.

05:48.666 --> 05:53.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We will see two large amendments
being proposed near the
top of this voting scheme.

05:54.166 --> 05:56.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
One will be that
straight repeal bill.

05:56.200 --> 06:00.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The other will be some version
of the Senate bill that we
have seen crafted recently.

06:02.100 --> 06:04.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Both of those are
expected to fail.

06:04.100 --> 06:08.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
After that, we will see perhaps
a day or many hours of a
flurry of different amendments.

06:09.933 --> 06:11.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Those will generally
require 60 votes.

06:11.600 --> 06:13.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It will be hard
for those to pass.

06:13.633 --> 06:18.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In the very end, Judy, we will
see probably this skinny repeal,
a sort of pared-down version

06:19.066 --> 06:20.166 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of repeal.

06:20.166 --> 06:21.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It will be the
Republicans' last vote.

06:21.600 --> 06:23.333 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They hope to get 50 on that.

06:23.333 --> 06:25.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It's not clear yet
how they will do that.

06:25.333 --> 06:29.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, Lisa, this
was quite an extraordinary
day, as you just showed in your

06:29.433 --> 06:30.433 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
piece.

06:30.433 --> 06:32.500 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
You were there.

06:32.500 --> 06:36.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What does this drama say about
the state of the Senate right
now, this debate, and the

06:37.200 --> 06:38.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
state of governing?

06:38.700 --> 06:41.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Judy, I have to
tell you, it was breathtaking.

06:41.333 --> 06:44.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It was rather unbelievable
to be in that Senate today.

06:44.000 --> 06:49.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For one, as Susan Collins and
Lisa Murkowski, the senators who
voted no, cast those opposing

06:49.733 --> 06:50.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
votes, they stood up.

06:50.933 --> 06:52.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They were emphatic
about their positions.

06:52.933 --> 06:57.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And at that time, Judy, looking
around the chamber, it was
clear that Republicans didn't

06:57.033 --> 06:59.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
know if they were going
to pass this bill.

06:59.100 --> 07:03.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I looked down below me, and I
saw Vice President Pence write
on a sheet of paper, "The Senate

07:03.733 --> 07:05.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
will be in recess."

07:05.533 --> 07:08.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That made it clear that they
were ready to lose this vote.

07:08.666 --> 07:12.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When Ron Johnson came in to
vote yes, they weren't sure
how it was going to end up.

07:12.800 --> 07:15.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Judy, I think that's
an indication of where
we are in general.

07:15.300 --> 07:17.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They don't know how
they finish this.

07:17.300 --> 07:20.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
They're glad to open
the process, but much
is still in flux.

07:20.033 --> 07:24.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They also don't know, we don't
know if anyone is willing to
compromise, as Senator McCain

07:24.600 --> 07:26.233 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
asked for today on the floor.

07:26.233 --> 07:28.233 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So much to watch.

07:28.233 --> 07:30.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Lisa Desjardins with
another long day at the
Capitol, thank you, Lisa.

07:30.766 --> 07:32.800 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: My pleasure.

07:32.800 --> 07:36.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And we will talk
to Montana Senator Jon Tester
about the day's drama right

07:37.500 --> 07:39.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
after the news summary.

07:39.666 --> 07:43.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
In the day's other news:
President Trump today
kept sawing on the tree
limb where he's recently

07:43.766 --> 07:46.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
placed his attorney
general, Jeff Sessions.

07:46.833 --> 07:51.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He charged that Sessions has
been very weak on investigating
Hillary Clinton, and needs

07:51.766 --> 07:53.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
to be -- quote --
"much tougher."

07:53.833 --> 07:57.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
As for whether Sessions will
keep his job, the president
said, "Time will tell."

07:57.933 --> 08:01.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
One of Mr. Trump's
advisers said he probably
wants Sessions to resign.

08:01.233 --> 08:05.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We will have a full report
later in the program.

08:05.066 --> 08:10.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The State Department denied
today that Secretary of
State Rex Tillerson is
increasingly frustrated

08:10.933 --> 08:12.933 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in his job.

08:12.933 --> 08:17.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Several news outlets reported
that the former ExxonMobil
chief is chafing at curbs on his

08:18.833 --> 08:20.500 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
independence.

08:20.500 --> 08:23.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
The reports said he's
told friends that he
may not last a year.

08:23.333 --> 08:26.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But spokesperson Heather
Nauert rejected any such talk.

08:26.533 --> 08:28.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
HEATHER NAUERT, State Department
Spokeswoman: That is false.

08:28.300 --> 08:30.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We have spoken
with the secretary.

08:30.333 --> 08:33.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The secretary has been very
clear he intends to stay
here at State Department.

08:33.800 --> 08:36.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We have a lot of work that is
left to be done ahead of us.

08:36.833 --> 08:38.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He recognizes that.

08:38.000 --> 08:40.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He is deeply engaged
in that work.

08:40.066 --> 08:44.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Nauert said
that Tillerson is currently
taking a little time off.

08:44.133 --> 08:49.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The U.S. House of
Representatives today
voted overwhelmingly to
impose new sanctions on

08:50.500 --> 08:53.366 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Russia, partly over its
meddling in the 2016 election.

08:53.366 --> 08:58.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This bars President Trump
from relaxing the penalties
without congressional approval.

09:00.333 --> 09:03.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Meanwhile, in the Russia
investigations, the president's
son-in-law, Jared Kushner, met

09:03.600 --> 09:06.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
privately with the House
Intelligence Committee.

09:06.733 --> 09:11.733 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And former Trump campaign
