broadside on Twitter, declaring:
"Attorney General Jeff Sessions

23:18.900 --> 23:22.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
has taken a very weak
position on Hillary Clinton
crimes and intel leakers."

23:24.666 --> 23:27.600 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, yesterday, another
tweet that called
Sessions "our beleaguered
A.G." and plaintively

23:28.866 --> 23:31.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
asked why he's not
investigating Hillary Clinton.

23:31.233 --> 23:33.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So, what is next?

23:33.400 --> 23:35.433 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The president said this today:

23:35.433 --> 23:39.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
DONALD TRUMP: I want
the attorney general
to be much tougher on
leaks from intelligence

23:39.766 --> 23:41.200 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
agencies.

23:41.200 --> 23:43.000 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We will see what happens.

23:43.000 --> 23:45.166 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Time will tell.

23:45.166 --> 23:49.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Sessions
was a veteran Republican
senator from Alabama,
and in early 2016 became

23:50.433 --> 23:55.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
